Aura of Terror	SOURCEPAGE:p.	SCHOOL:Necromancy	CLASSES:Necromancer=6	CASTTIME:1 standard action	RANGE:30-ft.-radius emanation centered on you	DURATION:(CASTERLEVEL) minutes	SAVEINFO:Will negates; see text	SPELLRES:Yes	DESC:You speak a few curt words and your face is briefly overlaid with the image of a violet-shaded skull. The skull fades, but the nimbus of violet light remains around you. You become surrounded by an aura of fear, granting you a frightful presence not unlike that of a dragon. Whenever you charge or attack, you inspire fear in all creatures within 30 feet that have fewer Hit Dice than your caster level. Each potentially affected opponent must succeed on a Will save or become shaken-a condition that lasts until the opponent is out of range. A successful save leaves that opponent immune to your frightful presence for 24 hours. If you cast this spell when you already have the frightful presence ability or a fear aura, the existing ability becomes more effective in the following ways:	DESC:* The radius of the area affected by the ability increases by 10 feet.	DESC:* The DC of your frightful presence ability increases by 2.	DESC:* Creatures that would normally be shaken by your fear aura are frightened instead, and creatures that would normally be frightened are panicked.
