Stunning Finale	SOURCEPAGE:p.859	SCHOOL:Enfeebling	CLASSES:Bard=5	CASTTIME:1 immediate action	TARGETAREA:Up to 3 creatures, no two of which can be more than 30 ft. apart	DURATION:1 round	SAVEINFO:Fortitude partial; see text	SPELLRES:Yes	DESC:You must have a bardic performance in effect to perform this song. With a flourish, you immediately end your bardic performance, assaulting the senses of the targets with your finale. Each target is stunned for 1 round. On a successful Saving Throw, a target is staggered for 1 round.
Summon Instrument	SOURCEPAGE:p.859	SCHOOL:Summoning|Jingle	CLASSES:Bard=0	TARGETAREA:One summoned handheld musical instrument	SAVEINFO:None	SPELLRES:No	DESC:This song summons one handheld musical instrument of your choice. This instrument appears in your hands or at your feet (your choice). The instrument is typical for its type. Only one instrument appears per performing, and it will play only for you. You can't summon an instrument too large to be held in two hands. The summoned instrument disappears at the end of this song.
Sword Madrigal	SOURCEPAGE:p.859	SCHOOL:Enhancing	CLASSES:Bard=2	SAVEINFO:Will negates (harmless)	SPELLRES:Yes (harmless)	DESC:You play the song of precision, granting allies a bonus to melee weapon attack rolls. Each round this song is in effect, allies within 30 feet of the bard gain a +1 morale bonus to Attack rolls with melee weapons.
